{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"So when you look out\nat the stars at night,"},{"time":3760,"text":"it's amazing what you can see."},{"time":5240,"text":"It's beautiful."},{"time":6720,"text":"But what's more amazing\nis what you can't see,"},{"time":9840,"text":"because what we know now"},{"time":11240,"text":"is that around every star\nor almost every star,"},{"time":14640,"text":"there's a planet,"},{"time":15920,"text":"or probably a few."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18120,"text":"So what this picture isn't showing you"},{"time":20240,"text":"are all the planets that we know about"},{"time":22400,"text":"out there in space."},{"time":24280,"text":"But when we think about planets,\nwe tend to think of faraway things"},{"time":27520,"text":"that are very different from our own."},{"time":29400,"text":"But here we are on a planet,"},{"time":31840,"text":"and there are so many things\nthat are amazing about Earth"},{"time":35160,"text":"that we're searching far and wide\nto find things that are like that."},{"time":39360,"text":"And when we're searching,\nwe're finding amazing things."},{"time":42880,"text":"But I want to tell you\nabout an amazing thing here on Earth."},{"time":47120,"text":"And that is that every minute,"},{"time":49880,"text":"400 pounds of hydrogen"},{"time":52320,"text":"and almost seven pounds of helium"},{"time":54960,"text":"escape from Earth into space."},{"time":58800,"text":"And this is gas that is going off\nand never coming back."},{"time":63440,"text":"So hydrogen, helium and many other things"},{"time":66480,"text":"make up what's known\nas the Earth's atmosphere."},{"time":69360,"text":"The atmosphere is just these gases\nthat form a thin blue line"},{"time":73200,"text":"that's seen here from\nthe International Space Station,"},{"time":76440,"text":"a photograph that some astronauts took."},{"time":79200,"text":"And this tenuous veneer around our planet"},{"time":82600,"text":"is what allows life to flourish."},{"time":84960,"text":"It protects our planet\nfrom too many impacts,"},{"time":87840,"text":"from meteorites and the like."},{"time":89880,"text":"And it's such an amazing phenomenon"},{"time":93680,"text":"that the fact that it's disappearing"},{"time":96520,"text":"should frighten you,\nat least a little bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100160,"text":"So this process is something that I study"},{"time":103480,"text":"and it's called atmospheric escape."},{"time":106680,"text":"So atmospheric escape\nis not specific to planet Earth."},{"time":111280,"text":"It's part of what it means\nto be a planet, if you ask me,"},{"time":115040,"text":"because planets, not just here on Earth\nbut throughout the universe,"},{"time":119400,"text":"can undergo atmospheric escape."},{"time":122000,"text":"And the way it happens actually tells us\nabout planets themselves."},{"time":127920,"text":"Because when you think\nabout the solar system,"},{"time":130600,"text":"you might think about this picture here."},{"time":133800,"text":"And you would say, well,\nthere are eight planets, maybe nine."},{"time":137240,"text":"So for those of you\nwho are stressed by this picture,"},{"time":139760,"text":"I will add somebody for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142400,"text":"Courtesy of New Horizons,\nwe're including Pluto."},{"time":146160,"text":"And the thing here is,"},{"time":147400,"text":"for the purposes of this talk\nand atmospheric escape,"},{"time":150160,"text":"Pluto is a planet in my mind,"},{"time":152200,"text":"in the same way that planets\naround other stars that we can't see"},{"time":156160,"text":"are also planets."},{"time":157960,"text":"So fundamental characteristics of planets"},{"time":160680,"text":"include the fact that they are bodies"},{"time":163720,"text":"that are bound together by gravity."},{"time":165560,"text":"So it's a lot of material\njust stuck together"},{"time":168080,"text":"with this attractive force."},{"time":170240,"text":"And these bodies are so big\nand have so much gravity."},{"time":173120,"text":"That's why they're round."},{"time":174440,"text":"So when you look at all of these,"},{"time":176080,"text":"including Pluto,"},{"time":177320,"text":"they're round."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"So you can see that gravity\nis really at play here."},{"time":181760,"text":"But another fundamental\ncharacteristic about planets"},{"time":185080,"text":"is what you don't see here,"},{"time":186840,"text":"and that's the star, the Sun,"},{"time":189440,"text":"that all of the planets\nin the solar system are orbiting around."},{"time":193200,"text":"And that's fundamentally driving\natmospheric escape."},{"time":197760,"text":"The reason that fundamentally stars\ndrive atmospheric escape from planets"},{"time":203120,"text":"is because stars offer planets\nparticles and light and heat"},{"time":208520,"text":"that can cause the atmospheres to go away."},{"time":211640,"text":"So if you think of a hot-air balloon,"},{"time":213480,"text":"or you look at this picture\nof lanterns in Thailand at a festival,"},{"time":217640,"text":"you can see that hot air\ncan propel gasses upward."},{"time":221160,"text":"And if you have enough energy and heating,"},{"time":223440,"text":"which our Sun does,"},{"time":224800,"text":"that gas, which is so light\nand only bound by gravity,"},{"time":228720,"text":"it can escape into space."},{"time":231600,"text":"And so this is what's actually\ncausing atmospheric escape"},{"time":235560,"text":"here on Earth and also on other planets --"},{"time":238280,"text":"that interplay\nbetween heating from the star"},{"time":241000,"text":"and overcoming the force\nof gravity on the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245000,"text":"So I've told you that it happens"},{"time":246760,"text":"at the rate of 400 pounds\na minute for hydrogen"},{"time":250120,"text":"and almost seven pounds for helium."},{"time":253040,"text":"But what does that look like?"},{"time":254720,"text":"Well, even in the '80s,"},{"time":256560,"text":"we took pictures of the Earth"},{"time":258320,"text":"in the ultraviolet"},{"time":259800,"text":"using NASA's Dynamic Explorer spacecraft."},{"time":262720,"text":"So these two images of the Earth"},{"time":264560,"text":"show you what that glow\nof escaping hydrogen looks like,"},{"time":268320,"text":"shown in red."},{"time":269600,"text":"And you can also see other features\nlike oxygen and nitrogen"},{"time":273240,"text":"in that white glimmer"},{"time":274720,"text":"in the circle showing you the auroras"},{"time":277080,"text":"and also some wisps around the tropics."},{"time":280000,"text":"So these are pictures\nthat conclusively show us"},{"time":283040,"text":"that our atmosphere isn't just\ntightly bound to us here on Earth"},{"time":286760,"text":"but it's actually\nreaching out far into space,"},{"time":290400,"text":"and at an alarming rate, I might add."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293080,"text":"But the Earth is not alone\nin undergoing atmospheric escape."},{"time":296920,"text":"Mars, our nearest neighbor,\nis much smaller than Earth,"},{"time":300400,"text":"so it has much less gravity\nwith which to hold on to its atmosphere."},{"time":304200,"text":"And so even though Mars has an atmosphere,"},{"time":306440,"text":"we can see it's much thinner\nthan the Earth's."},{"time":308680,"text":"Just look at the surface."},{"time":310160,"text":"You see craters indicating\nthat it didn't have an atmosphere"},{"time":313640,"text":"that could stop those impacts."},{"time":315520,"text":"Also, we see that it's the \"red planet,\""},{"time":318320,"text":"and atmospheric escape plays a role"},{"time":320880,"text":"in Mars being red."},{"time":322480,"text":"That's because we think\nMars used to have a wetter past,"},{"time":326080,"text":"and when water had enough energy,\nit broke up into hydrogen and oxygen,"},{"time":330680,"text":"and hydrogen being so light,\nit escaped into space,"},{"time":334440,"text":"and the oxygen that was left"},{"time":336400,"text":"oxidized or rusted the ground,"},{"time":338240,"text":"making that familiar\nrusty red color that we see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342960,"text":"So it's fine to look at pictures of Mars"},{"time":344920,"text":"and say that atmospheric escape\nprobably happened,"},{"time":347400,"text":"but NASA has a probe that's currently\nat Mars called the MAVEN satellite,"},{"time":351520,"text":"and its actual job\nis to study atmospheric escape."},{"time":355080,"text":"It's the Mars Atmosphere\nand Volatile Evolution spacecraft."},{"time":359680,"text":"And results from it have already\nshown pictures very similar"},{"time":363360,"text":"to what you've seen here on Earth."},{"time":365280,"text":"We've long known that Mars\nwas losing its atmosphere,"},{"time":367800,"text":"but we have some stunning pictures."},{"time":369600,"text":"Here, for example,\nyou can see in the red circle"},{"time":372760,"text":"is the size of Mars,"},{"time":374280,"text":"and in blue you can see the hydrogen\nescaping away from the planet."},{"time":378480,"text":"So it's reaching out more than 10 times\nthe size of the planet,"},{"time":382040,"text":"far enough away that it's\nno longer bound to that planet."},{"time":384760,"text":"It's escaping off into space."},{"time":386760,"text":"And this helps us confirm ideas,"},{"time":389000,"text":"like why Mars is red,\nfrom that lost hydrogen."},{"time":392520,"text":"But hydrogen isn't\nthe only gas that's lost."},{"time":395120,"text":"I mentioned helium on Earth\nand some oxygen and nitrogen,"},{"time":398320,"text":"and from MAVEN we can also look\nat the oxygen being lost from Mars."},{"time":402120,"text":"And you can see\nthat because oxygen is heavier,"},{"time":404600,"text":"it can't get as far as the hydrogen,"},{"time":407760,"text":"but it's still escaping\naway from the planet."},{"time":409960,"text":"You don't see it all confined\ninto that red circle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413800,"text":"So the fact that we not only see\natmospheric escape on our own planet"},{"time":417840,"text":"but we can study it elsewhere\nand send spacecraft"},{"time":421480,"text":"allows us to learn\nabout the past of planets"},{"time":424600,"text":"but also about planets in general"},{"time":426880,"text":"and Earth's future."},{"time":428680,"text":"So one way we actually\ncan learn about the future"},{"time":431360,"text":"is by planets so far away\nthat we can't see."},{"time":435440,"text":"And I should just note though,\nbefore I go on to that,"},{"time":438520,"text":"I'm not going to show you\nphotos like this of Pluto,"},{"time":441000,"text":"which might be disappointing,"},{"time":442440,"text":"but that's because we don't have them yet."},{"time":444480,"text":"But the New Horizons mission\nis currently studying atmospheric escape"},{"time":447760,"text":"being lost from the planet."},{"time":449120,"text":"So stay tuned and look out for that."},{"time":451560,"text":"But the planets\nthat I did want to talk about"},{"time":453720,"text":"are known as transiting exoplanets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456040,"text":"So any planet orbiting a star\nthat's not our Sun"},{"time":459840,"text":"is called an exoplanet,\nor extrasolar planet."},{"time":462800,"text":"And these planets that we call transiting"},{"time":465280,"text":"have the special feature"},{"time":466560,"text":"that if you look\nat that star in the middle,"},{"time":468680,"text":"you'll see that actually it's blinking."},{"time":471080,"text":"And the reason that it's blinking"},{"time":472960,"text":"is because there are planets\nthat are going past it all the time,"},{"time":477000,"text":"and it's that special orientation"},{"time":479160,"text":"where the planets are blocking\nthe light from the star"},{"time":481960,"text":"that allows us to see that light blinking."},{"time":484960,"text":"And by surveying the stars\nin the night sky"},{"time":487840,"text":"for this blinking motion,"},{"time":489280,"text":"we are able to find planets."},{"time":490960,"text":"This is how we've now been able\nto detect over 5,000 planets"},{"time":495160,"text":"in our own Milky Way,"},{"time":496400,"text":"and we know there are\nmany more out there, like I mentioned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499280,"text":"So when we look at the light\nfrom these stars,"},{"time":502200,"text":"what we see, like I said,\nis not the planet itself,"},{"time":505720,"text":"but you actually see\na dimming of the light"},{"time":507800,"text":"that we can record in time."},{"time":509480,"text":"So the light drops as the planet\ndecreases in front of the star,"},{"time":512919,"text":"and that's that blinking\nthat you saw before."},{"time":515360,"text":"So not only do we detect the planets"},{"time":517200,"text":"but we can look at this light\nin different wavelengths."},{"time":520039,"text":"So I mentioned looking at the Earth\nand Mars in ultraviolet light."},{"time":524159,"text":"If we look at transiting exoplanets\nwith the Hubble Space Telescope,"},{"time":527800,"text":"we find that in the ultraviolet,"},{"time":529920,"text":"you see much bigger blinking,\nmuch less light from the star,"},{"time":533600,"text":"when the planet is passing in front."},{"time":535400,"text":"And we think this is because you have\nan extended atmosphere of hydrogen"},{"time":538840,"text":"all around the planet"},{"time":540080,"text":"that's making it look puffier"},{"time":541600,"text":"and thus blocking\nmore of the light that you see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544880,"text":"So using this technique,\nwe've actually been able to discover"},{"time":547800,"text":"a few transiting exoplanets\nthat are undergoing atmospheric escape."},{"time":552080,"text":"And these planets\ncan be called hot Jupiters,"},{"time":554920,"text":"for some of the ones we've found."},{"time":556560,"text":"And that's because\nthey're gas planets like Jupiter,"},{"time":559160,"text":"but they're so close to their star,"},{"time":560960,"text":"about a hundred times closer than Jupiter."},{"time":563240,"text":"And because there's all this\nlightweight gas that's ready to escape,"},{"time":566720,"text":"and all this heating from the star,"},{"time":568440,"text":"you have completely catastrophic rates\nof atmospheric escape."},{"time":572280,"text":"So unlike our 400 pounds per minute\nof hydrogen being lost on Earth,"},{"time":576920,"text":"for these planets,"},{"time":578200,"text":"you're losing 1.3 billion\npounds of hydrogen every minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583320,"text":"So you might think, well,\ndoes this make the planet cease to exist?"},{"time":587680,"text":"And this is a question\nthat people wondered"},{"time":589720,"text":"when they looked at our solar system,"},{"time":591560,"text":"because planets\ncloser to the Sun are rocky,"},{"time":593920,"text":"and planets further away\nare bigger and more gaseous."},{"time":596880,"text":"Could you have started\nwith something like Jupiter"},{"time":599280,"text":"that was actually close to the Sun,"},{"time":601000,"text":"and get rid of all the gas in it?"},{"time":602640,"text":"We now think that if you start\nwith something like a hot Jupiter,"},{"time":605720,"text":"you actually can't end up\nwith Mercury or the Earth."},{"time":608560,"text":"But if you started with something smaller,"},{"time":610760,"text":"it's possible that enough gas\nwould have gotten away"},{"time":613560,"text":"that it would have\nsignificantly impacted it"},{"time":615720,"text":"and left you with something very different\nthan what you started with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619080,"text":"So all of this sounds sort of general,"},{"time":621000,"text":"and we might think about the solar system,"},{"time":623560,"text":"but what does this have to do\nwith us here on Earth?"},{"time":626360,"text":"Well, in the far future,"},{"time":628160,"text":"the Sun is going to get brighter."},{"time":630320,"text":"And as that happens,"},{"time":631560,"text":"the heating that we find from the Sun\nis going to become very intense."},{"time":635600,"text":"In the same way that you see\ngas streaming off from a hot Jupiter,"},{"time":639960,"text":"gas is going to stream off from the Earth."},{"time":642320,"text":"And so what we can look forward to,"},{"time":644520,"text":"or at least prepare for,"},{"time":646600,"text":"is the fact that in the far future,"},{"time":648440,"text":"the Earth is going to look more like Mars."},{"time":651240,"text":"Our hydrogen, from water\nthat is broken down,"},{"time":654000,"text":"is going to escape\ninto space more rapidly,"},{"time":656440,"text":"and we're going to be left\nwith this dry, reddish planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660960,"text":"So don't fear, it's not\nfor a few billion years,"},{"time":663480,"text":"so there's some time to prepare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":666160,"text":"But I wanted you\nto be aware of what's going on,"},{"time":669000,"text":"not just in the future,"},{"time":670280,"text":"but atmospheric escape\nis happening as we speak."},{"time":673520,"text":"So there's a lot of amazing science\nthat you hear about happening in space"},{"time":677040,"text":"and planets that are far away,"},{"time":679000,"text":"and we are studying these planets\nto learn about these worlds."},{"time":682240,"text":"But as we learn about Mars\nor exoplanets like hot Jupiters,"},{"time":686960,"text":"we find things like atmospheric escape"},{"time":690000,"text":"that tell us a lot more\nabout our planet here on Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693760,"text":"So consider that the next time\nyou think that space is far away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697840,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699080,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}